.\" Man page for alph(1) — Alpheus Context Engine Framework CLI
.TH ALPH 1 "2026-03-12" "alph 0.1.25" "Alpheus Context Engine Framework"
.SH NAME
alph \- git-backed context management for LLMs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B alph
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.I COMMAND
.RI [ ARGS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B alph
is the CLI for the Alpheus Context Engine Framework (AlpheusCEF).
It manages structured context nodes organized into pools within registries,
all backed by git for versioning, diffs, and collaboration.
.PP
Context flows through a funnel: registry \(-> pool \(-> node. Each level
carries a
.B context
field that orients humans and LLMs to the purpose of that entity.
.PP
Nodes are Markdown files with YAML frontmatter stored in
.B snapshots/
(point-in-time captures) or
.B live/
(pointers to external resources that resolve on demand).
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-reg ", " \-\-registry " " \fITEXT\fR
Override registry: ID, name, or remote git URL.
Scopes pool resolution to this registry for one invocation.
.TP
.BI \-\-branch " TEXT"
Override git branch for remote operations.
Useful with ad-hoc \fB\-\-registry\fR URLs that have no config entry.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS "Node commands"
.TP
.B alph add
Create a context node in a pool.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-context " " \fITEXT\fR
Context description for this node. Required.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-pool " " \fITEXT\fR
Pool path or name. Defaults to \fBdefault_pool\fR from config.
.TP
.BI \-\-creator " TEXT"
Creator email address. Defaults to \fBcreator\fR from config.
.TP
.BI \-\-type " TEXT"
\fBsnapshot\fR (or \fBsnap\fR) or \fBlive\fR. Default: snapshot.
.TP
.BI \-\-content " TEXT"
Optional Markdown body.
.TP
.BI \-\-status " TEXT"
\fBactive\fR (default), \fBarchived\fR, or \fBsuppressed\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B alph list
List nodes in a pool with frontmatter summary.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-pool " " \fITEXT\fR
Pool path or name.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-status " " \fITEXT\fR
Filter by status: \fBarchived\fR, \fBsuppressed\fR, \fBall\fR,
or comma-separated (e.g. \fBarchived,suppressed\fR).
Default: active only.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fITEXT\fR
Output format: \fBconsole\fR (default), \fBjson\fR, \fByaml\fR, \fBcsv\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-pull
Pull latest changes before listing (RW clones only).
.RE
.TP
.B alph show \fINODE_ID\fR
Display full node content formatted for terminal.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-pool " " \fITEXT\fR
Pool path or name.
.TP
.B \-\-pull
Pull latest changes before showing (RW clones only).
.RE
.TP
.B alph validate
Check all nodes in a pool against schema.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-pool " " \fITEXT\fR
Pool path or name.
.TP
.B \-\-pull
Pull latest changes before validating (RW clones only).
.RE
.TP
.B alph defaults
Show the currently resolved defaults (registry, pool, creator).
.SS "Registry commands (alph registry | alph reg)"
.PP
When no subcommand is given, defaults to \fBregistry list\fR.
.TP
.B alph registry init
Create a registry and register it in the global config.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-\-pool\-home " TEXT"
Directory or git remote URL. Required.
.TP
.BI \-\-id " TEXT"
Machine identifier for the registry. Required.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-context " " \fITEXT\fR
Human/LLM-readable description. Required.
.TP
.BI \-\-name " TEXT"
Optional human-readable name.
.TP
.BI \-\-mode " TEXT"
Access mode: \fBro\fR or \fBrw\fR.
Auto-detected if omitted (ro for remote, rw for local).
.TP
.BI \-\-clone\-path " TEXT"
Local directory for RW clone (remote registries only).
.TP
.BI \-\-branch " TEXT"
Git branch for RO reads and RW clone checkout.
.TP
.BR \-\-auto\-push " | " \-\-no\-auto\-push
Push after commit. Default: true for RW remote, false for local.
.TP
.BR \-\-auto\-pull " | " \-\-no\-auto\-pull
Pull before read. Default: true for RW remote, false for local.
.RE
.TP
.B alph registry list
List all registries known from the config file tree.
.TP
.B alph registry check \fR[\fIREGISTRY_ID\fR]
Verify a registry is reachable.
Pass \fBall\fR to check every registry.
Defaults to \fBdefault_registry\fR when no argument is given.
.TP
.B alph registry clone \fR[\fIREGISTRY_ID\fR]
Clone a remote registry locally for RW access.
Defaults to \fBdefault_registry\fR when no argument is given.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-\-clone\-path " PATH"
Local directory to clone into. Default: \fI~/.cache/alph/clones/<hash>/\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B alph registry pull \fR[\fIREGISTRY_ID\fR]
Pull latest changes for a cloned remote registry (git pull \-\-ff\-only).
Defaults to \fBdefault_registry\fR when no argument is given.
.TP
.B alph registry status \fR[\fIREGISTRY_ID\fR]
Show registry status: mode, clone state, branch, auto_push, and path details.
Defaults to \fBdefault_registry\fR when no argument is given.
.SS "Pool commands (alph pool)"
.PP
When no subcommand is given, defaults to \fBpool list\fR.
.TP
.B alph pool init
Create a pool inside a registry.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-reg ", " \-\-registry " " \fITEXT\fR
Registry ID or name. Defaults to \fBdefault_registry\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-name " TEXT"
Pool name (machine identifier, used as directory name). Required.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-context " " \fITEXT\fR
Human/LLM-readable description. Required.
.TP
.BI \-\-type " TEXT"
Pool type: \fBsubdir\fR (default) or \fBrepo\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B alph pool list
List pools in a registry (configured and discovered on disk).
.SS "Config commands (alph config)"
.PP
When no subcommand is given, defaults to \fBconfig list\fR.
.TP
.B alph config list
List all config files in the discovery tree, showing which exist
and which registries each declares.
.TP
.B alph config show \fIPATH\fR
Display a config file with syntax highlighting.
.TP
.B alph config show\-all
Display the fully merged config with all default values filled in.
Shows the resolved configuration as alph sees it.
.TP
.B alph config check
Check all config files for unknown or legacy keys.
Reports typos like \fBclone_dir\fR instead of \fBclone_path\fR.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B alph
loads configuration from a cascade of YAML files. Priority (highest wins):
CLI overrides > cwd-nearest config > ... > global config > defaults.
.TP
.I ~/.config/alph/config.yaml
Global config (base layer). Created by \fBalph registry init\fR.
.TP
.I config.yaml
Local config files found walking up from the current directory.
.PP
Top-level config keys:
.RS
.TP
.B creator
Default creator email for new nodes.
.TP
.B auto_commit
Auto-commit after node creation (default: false).
.TP
.B default_registry
Registry ID used when no \fB\-\-registry\fR flag is given.
.TP
.B default_pool
Pool name used when no \fB\-\-pool\fR flag is given.
.TP
.B register_subdir_pools
When true, \fBpool init\fR writes pool entries to the config file
in addition to the pool-local \fI.alph.yaml\fR dotfile.
Default: false (subdir pools are discovered from the filesystem).
.TP
.B registries
Map of registry IDs to registry entries.
.RE
.PP
Registry entry keys:
.RS
.TP
.B pool_home
Local path or git remote URL (e.g. \fIgit@github.com:org/repo.git:/subpath\fR).
.TP
.B context
Human/LLM-readable description.
.TP
.B name
Optional human-readable name.
.TP
.B mode
\fBro\fR (read-only) or \fBrw\fR (read-write). Auto-detected for remote URLs.
.TP
.B clone_path
Local directory for RW clone (remote registries only).
.TP
.B branch
Git branch for RO reads and RW clone checkout.
.TP
.B auto_push
Push after commit (default: true for RW remote).
.TP
.B auto_pull
Pull before read (default: true for RW remote).
.TP
.B pools
Map of pool names to pool metadata (\fBcontext\fR, \fBtype\fR).
.RE
.SH POOL STRUCTURE
Each pool directory contains:
.RS
.TP
.I snapshots/
Point-in-time context nodes (Markdown with YAML frontmatter).
.TP
.I live/
Live nodes that point to external resources.
.TP
.I .alph.yaml
Pool-local metadata: context, creator, and creation date.
Created by \fBpool init\fR.
.RE
.SH NODE SCHEMA
Node frontmatter fields:
.RS
.TP
.B schema_version
Schema version (currently 1).
.TP
.B id
Deterministic identifier: sha256(source + context)[:12].
.TP
.B timestamp
ISO 8601 creation timestamp.
.TP
.B source
Origin of the context (e.g. URL, conversation, document).
.TP
.B node_type
\fBsnapshot\fR or \fBlive\fR.
.TP
.B context
Human/LLM-readable description.
.TP
.B creator
Email of the node creator.
.TP
.B status
\fBactive\fR (default), \fBarchived\fR, or \fBsuppressed\fR.
.TP
.B tags
Optional list of tags.
.TP
.B related_to
Optional list of related node IDs. Supports cross-pool
(\fIpool::node_id\fR) and cross-registry (\fIregistry::pool::node_id\fR) references.
.TP
.B meta
Optional metadata dictionary (e.g. \fBprovider\fR, \fBresolves_to\fR for live nodes).
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ALPH_CONFIG_DIR
Override the global config directory (default: \fI~/.config/alph/\fR).
Primarily used for testing.
.TP
.B GITHUB_TOKEN\fR, \fBGH_TOKEN
GitHub personal access token for remote registry API reads.
Falls back to \fBgh auth token\fR.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/alph/config.yaml
Global configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/alph/secrets.yaml
Secrets file (gitignored).
.TP
.I ~/.cache/alph/clones/
Default location for remote registry clones.
.SH EXAMPLES
Create a local registry and pool:
.PP
.RS
.nf
alph registry init \-\-pool\-home ~/context \-\-id personal \-c "Personal context"
alph pool init \-\-name projects \-c "Active projects"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Add a snapshot node:
.PP
.RS
.nf
alph add \-c "Decided to use PostgreSQL for the new service"
.fi
.RE
.PP
List nodes, show one:
.PP
.RS
.nf
alph list
alph show a1b2c3d4e5f6
.fi
.RE
.PP
Set up a read-only remote registry:
.PP
.RS
.nf
alph registry init \-\-pool\-home git@github.com:org/repo.git:/registry \\
    \-\-id shared \-c "Shared team context" \-\-mode ro \-\-branch main
alph list \-\-registry shared \-\-pool standards
.fi
.RE
.PP
Check config for typos:
.PP
.RS
.nf
alph config check
alph config show\-all
.fi
.RE
.SH MCP SERVER
.B alph\-mcp
exposes the same core functions as MCP tools for LLM integration.
It is installed alongside \fBalph\fR and can be configured as an MCP server
in Claude, Cursor, or other MCP-compatible clients.
